```{r}
#| label: tbl-demographics
#| tbl-cap: "Participant Demographics by Group"
#| echo: false

library(knitr)
library(kableExtra)

# Create a data frame for the table
data <- data.frame(
  Characteristic = c("Age (years)", "Gender", "   Male", "   Female", "BMI (kg/m²)", "Physical Activity (min/week)"),
  `Group 1 (n=25)` = c("35.2 ± 8.4", "", "12 (48%)", "13 (52%)", "24.3 ± 3.2", "156 ± 45"),
  `Group 2 (n=25)` = c("36.5 ± 7.9", "", "13 (52%)", "12 (48%)", "25.1 ± 3.5", "148 ± 52"),
  `Group 3 (n=25)` = c("34.8 ± 8.1", "", "14 (56%)", "11 (44%)", "24.7 ± 3.0", "152 ± 48")
)

# Create the table
kable(data, format = "latex", booktabs = TRUE, align = c("l", "c", "c", "c")) %>%
  kable_styling(latex_options = c("striped")) %>%
  row_spec(0, bold = TRUE) %>%
  row_spec(1, hline_after = TRUE) %>%
  row_spec(4, hline_after = TRUE)
```

```{r}
#| label: tbl-outcomes
#| tbl-cap: "Primary Outcomes by Group at Baseline, 6 Weeks, and 12 Weeks"
#| echo: false

# Create a data frame for the outcomes table
outcomes <- data.frame(
  Measure = c("Physical Activity Self-Efficacy", "   Baseline", "   6 Weeks", "   12 Weeks", 
              "Exercise Enjoyment", "   Baseline", "   6 Weeks", "   12 Weeks",
              "Weekly Exercise Duration (min)", "   Baseline", "   6 Weeks", "   12 Weeks"),
  `Group 1 (n=25)` = c("", "3.2 ± 0.8", "3.8 ± 0.9*", "4.2 ± 0.7**", 
                        "", "2.9 ± 0.7", "3.5 ± 0.8*", "4.0 ± 0.6**",
                        "", "156 ± 45", "185 ± 52*", "210 ± 48**"),
  `Group 2 (n=25)` = c("", "3.3 ± 0.7", "3.5 ± 0.8", "3.7 ± 0.8*", 
                        "", "3.0 ± 0.8", "3.3 ± 0.7", "3.5 ± 0.7*",
                        "", "148 ± 52", "165 ± 48", "175 ± 50*"),
  `Group 3 (n=25)` = c("", "3.2 ± 0.8", "3.3 ± 0.7", "3.4 ± 0.8", 
                        "", "2.8 ± 0.9", "3.0 ± 0.8", "3.1 ± 0.7",
                        "", "152 ± 48", "158 ± 50", "162 ± 52")
)

# Create the outcomes table
kable(outcomes, format = "latex", booktabs = TRUE, align = c("l", "c", "c", "c")) %>%
  kable_styling(latex_options = c("striped")) %>%
  row_spec(0, bold = TRUE) %>%
  row_spec(c(4, 8), hline_after = TRUE) %>%
  add_footnote("*p < .05 compared to baseline; **p < .01 compared to baseline", notation = "none")
```

The three groups were comparable on baseline characteristics with no significant differences in age, gender distribution, BMI, or weekly physical activity levels (all $p > .05$).
